reviews.text: Beautiful hotel with amazing service and views of the harbor.  Excellent breakfasts at both venues, nice outdoor pool.  Highly recommended.  More reasonable than other 5 star hotels in the area.

Always a fantastic hotel to stay at (and I travel the world)!  The only play to stay in Hong Kong, for work or pleasure.  Fantastic staff, service, food, and accommodations.
A truly unique experience that set the standard for others to follow!

Very pleasant experience. The staff and facilities were top notch. Special mention to Hayden in the Horizon Club Lounge, he was absolutely fantastic. He was extremely attentive and helpful in every regard, and a genuine person at that. I will look back on my experience at Shangri-La with fond memories.

From the pick up at the airport through to saying good bye when we left, we were made to feel like valued and welcomed guests by everyone we met. The service, the food and drinks, and the accommodation all exceeded our expectations. Thank you for such a wonderful stay.

Room was a good size and well lighted. Bed was very large for a king size. Pillows were too soft for my liking however but that is just me. TV programmes were sufficient. Bathroom was a good size and had everything we needed. However the best thing is the location above Pacific Place where you are able to get almost everything you need. The Admiralty MRT station is minutes away. Very central to get anywhere.

html_attributions: Lobster Bar and Grill at Island Shangri-La, Hong Kong

reviews.text: Celebrated my managers birthday here. Love the lobster bisque! Nice ambience and great love music

One of our favourite bar at this end of the town with great drinks, ambience and live music in the evening. 

Old world charm decor that's quite timeless. Service is typical Shangri-la high standard - attentive yet non intrusive. Drinks and cocktails are among some of the best quality in town. They do the classics superbly well. The easy listening live jazz band adds to the wonderful ambience. 

There are also a good selection of food and a dining area. 

It does get a bit busy and noisy at weekends but otherwise is a lovely place for a date or a quiet evening drink.
Good food and service with reasonable price

Nice place for a celebration dinner. Atmosphere is ok with a live band but  a bit on the noisy side with the people talking quite loud. The staff are very helpful and friendly. 5 out of 5
Food is OK, I give 3.5 out of 5 for food and price. The best dish is the beef which is just right, very soft but could be a bit more juicy. Fish is ok not dry, scallop is just a bit over cooked on the dry side. Soup is good. Crab cake is on the dry side but still OK.
Nice place for dinner, love their signature menu. Excellent crab cake and lobster bisque.

reviews.text:
環境座位舒適，服務非常好。
以龍蝦作主打，龍蝦湯濃厚鮮甜，主餐龍蝦有點略嫌太熟。點的medium rare牛扒煎得恰到好處，但外皮有點焦苦，小扣分。
甜品和前菜都很出色，整體而言不錯。
Celebrated my managers birthday here. Love the lobster bisque! Nice ambience and great love music
